details.title: first_person_description
details.body: You describe yourself as someone who has a mature and streetwise view of other people and their views. Your first instinct is likely to be to trust other people, but you do know that others can let you down. Thus, while you are a loyal friend and colleague, you do not take everything on trust. Your results indicate that you tend to have an attitude towards others that is built on openness and a view that people are imperfect and sometimes need help. Therefore, when you deal with other people, you will search for a mutually acceptable outcome, because you know that you need to work together. In this way, you are probably able to be direct, but are also able to temper your approach with sensitivity for what will keep relationships healthy and intact.

details.title: first_person_description
details.body: You come across as someone who is comfortable in social situations, but who also knows when to withdraw for periods of quiet reflection. Your results indicate that you are likely to be able to adapt your interpersonal approach, depending on the situation, with the result that you are able to connect easily with different types of people. However, you are just as likely to be found lost in thought as you are lost in conversation! When it comes to the energy you put into life, you're content being where the action is, but are also able to vary your level of enthusiasm so that you don't come across as being too attention-grabbing. Generally, you're the kind of person who has a good idea of the amount of excitement you would like - however, you can find too much 'down-time' de-motivating.

details.title: first_person_description
details.body: You seem to be the sort of person who prefers to weigh the extent to which tasks need to be structured, organized and planned. You are likely to be aware of the fact that there are things that need to be approached in a highly methodical manner, and equally, that there are occasions when action is more important than following a pre-planned approach.  Based on your results, you seem to be the type of person who can measure out the energy you invest in tasks, ramping up more when you have to do things you would normally avoid. This view of how work should be done is reinforced by the fact that you are likely to commit to tasks when you feel fully invested in the outcome, and it's this sense of ownership that gives you the confidence to do your best work.

details.title: first_person_description
details.body: You appear to take a balanced approach to solving problems. You are likely to be able to think of new and original ways of approaching situations, but not at the expense of ignoring well-established solutions, already known to work. This will often involve investigating problems by taking an open-ended view of what might work, and not being afraid to change things if necessary. Most likely, you will have an eye on whether something will be effective both now and in the future. The emphasis will probably be on juggling the facts and making changes, large or small, in order to make a decision that will stand the test of time.

details.title: first_person_description
details.body: You look as if you respond to pressure in a relaxed way but also know when to take things seriously. You seem to be able to let minor irritations go. Your results indicate that you are someone who is generally calm, and not the sort to dwell on things, but who is also 'on guard' at times. You listen to other people and take note of what they say, but are not prone to let criticism interfere with what you do. When it comes to managing your feelings, you tend to respond to situations in a measured manner, as you have a good understanding of your ability to cope. Indeed your friends and colleagues might well describe you as an even-tempered and positive person. By and large you probably feel well able to deal with most of what life hands you.

details.title: Candidate Description
details.body: You can get lost in your work, appreciating the value of devoting expertise to the execution of a task. You are at ease working in your own way, on your own terms.

details.title: Complement
details.body: You are sensitive, even-tempered, compassionate and compatible with many people. Since you are agreeable and enjoy multitasking and doing tasks on the fly in a relaxed, spontaneous way, you often work in a nonlinear fashion, accomplishing a little of this and a little of that.  Finally, you find that those with open-minds are just too flexible and those with too intense a work ethic are too inflexible for you.

details.title: Conflict
details.body: As a lover of people, you are fortunate that you work well with most sorts of people. Often sought out for your amicability, you may find that others may try to dominate and manipulate you, and you may have to adopt a certain amount of assertiveness to be respected. However, you may find that, because of your sensitivity and flexibility, you may be viewed as too laid back and engaging in the process of doing by some, who feel that you get lost in the weeds and are not task oriented enough. Also, others may worry about your emotional vulnerabilities at times.

environments.name: Allows for peer support in the pursuit of goals
Features a low key atmosphere that doesn’t seem overly competitive

personalityTypes.name: Openness
personalityTypes.description: Solving Problems (Openness) concerns how someone thinks about work problems, projects and challenges, how receptive they are to new or different information or approaches, and the way this influences their decision-making.

personalityTypes.name: Emotional Stability
personalityTypes.description: Managing pressure (Emotional Stability) concerns the manner in which someone deals with pressure and the way in which they control their emotions and underlying tension, in order to stay on task and cope with everyday challenges.

personalityTypes.name: Conscientiousness
personalityTypes.description: Delivering Results (Conscientiousness) concerns work style and how someone directs their efforts and attention toward completing tasks. The level of discipline, dedication, perseverance, organization and reliability are hallmark factors of this dimension.

personalityTypes.name: Extraversion
personalityTypes.description: Engaging with people (Extraversion) concerns someone’s interest, investment and comfort in developing relationships with others - customers, clients, work groups or colleagues.

personalityTypes.name: Agreeableness
personalityTypes.description: Influencing people (Agreeableness) concerns the way someone balances their emotional understanding of other people, and their respect for differing viewpoints, with the style in which they try to influence or negotiate with them.
